cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.IT 

The paper deals with the real-time monitoring of dynamic large-scale networks, specifically the global Internet, using topology changes information. This falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI) and system and control (cs.SY). The paper also uses graph theory measures and embeddings, which are related to data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper proposes a new geometric approach using Ollivier-Ricci curvature, which is related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and possibly social and information networks (cs.SI).
